body:
As can be seen from the token metrics available here -> [Bitmax Zendesk](https://bitmaxhelp.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/360060261774) and as detailed in the medium post here -> [Route Tokenomics]("https://routerprotocol.medium.com/an-introduction-to-route-tokenomics-investing-into-the-router-ecosystem-8852df26ef10"), 20% of private investor tokens vest immediately, and linear vesting starts for remaining tokens over the next 9 months. We propose to delay the start of this initial vesting by an **additional month**, so that vesting of the unvested portion starts one month after TGE, if there is a community quorum to achieve this. This will effectively delay the inflation by a month, and the overall vesting for these investors go from a 9-month to a 10-month cycle, with a one-month cliff.

Need 25% of **$ROUTE** holders in circulation to vote for quorum, and the option with single largest vote tally will win.

**Choices:**
**Yes** for delay investor vesting by a month; 
**No** for not delaying investor vesting;
